<h1 id="conclusions">Conclusions</h1>
<h3 id="conclusions-1">Conclusions</h3>
<p>The optimal grain storage policy…</p>
<ul>
<li><p>&lt;1&gt; would not fully stabilize food prices.</p></li>
<li><p>&lt;2&gt; would not prevent extreme hunger, yet it would reduce its frequency.</p></li>
<li><p>&lt;3&gt; is very sensitive to key parameters (price process, storage costs)</p></li>
<li><p>&lt;4&gt; might be outperformed by policies that attack poverty directly.</p></li>
<li><p>&lt;5&gt; in many cases, no better than accumulating financial assets.</p></li>
<li><p>&lt;6&gt; is more “active” when objective is avoiding extreme hunger.</p></li>
</ul>
